  1. Defining Problem Statement and Analysing basic metrics (10 Points)
    • We are trying to observe patterns in the Netflix data which can help us to take decision with respect to future plan
    • We are seeing patterns between type of content in various countries, top genres and their rating etc.
  • We are ultimately getting insights to make decisions about plans of content in various regions to improve the watching experience of the customers

In [ ]:
#Necessary initial column transformations/additions 
df['date_added']=pd.to_datetime(df['date_added'])
df['year_added']=df['date_added'].dt.year
df['month_added']=df['date_added'].dt.month
df['tot_seasons']=df['duration'].str.extract(r'(\d+) Season[s]?', expand=False).astype(float)
df['duration']=df['duration'].str.extract(r'(\d+) min', expand=False).astype(float)
df.rename(columns={'listed_in':'genre'},inplace=True)

#Univariate Analysis for continuous variables
cont_var=['duration','tot_seasons','release_year','year_added','month_added']
plt.figure(figsize=(10,15))
for i in range(1,len(cont_var)+1):
    plt.subplot(5,2,2*i-1)
    sns.distplot(df[cont_var[i-1]],kde=True)
    plt.subplot(5,2,2*i)
    sns.histplot(df[cont_var[i-1]],kde=True)
plt.show()

# Comparison of tv shows vs. movies.
country_top5=df['country'].value_counts()[:5].index.to_list()
genre_top5=genre_df['genre'].value_counts()[:5].index.to_list()
moviegenre_top5=genre_df[genre_df['type']=='Movie']['genre'].value_counts()[:5].index.to_list()
tvgenre_top5=genre_df[genre_df['type']=='TV Show']['genre'].value_counts()[:5].index.to_list()
plt.figure(figsize=(15,5))
plt.subplot(1,3,1)
sns.countplot(df[df['country'].isin(country_top5)],x='country',hue='type')
plt.title('movie/tv split in top5 country')
plt.subplot(1,3,2)
sns.countplot(genre_df[genre_df['genre'].isin(moviegenre_top5)],x='genre',hue='type')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.title('movie genre top5')
plt.subplot(1,3,3)
sns.countplot(genre_df[genre_df['genre'].isin(tvgenre_top5)],x='genre',hue='type')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.title('tv genre top5')
plt.show()

grouped = genre_df[genre_df['country'].isin(country_top5)].groupby(['country', 'genre']).size().reset_index(name='Count')

# Sort the data within each country group by count in descending order
grouped = grouped.sort_values(['country', 'Count'], ascending=[True, False])


top_5_genres = grouped.groupby('country').head(5)


temp=sns.barplot(data=top_5_genres, x='country', y='Count', hue='genre',palette='deep')

plt.setp(temp.get_legend().get_title(), fontsize='10')

# 7. Business Insights (10 Points) - Should include patterns observed in the data along with what you can infer from it
# We observe that every country has a particular month where maximum titles are added. This maybe due to the holiday months
# More movies affinity maybe there in some countries compared to others
# Based on Top genres observed in top countries content we can strategize our content creation 
# 100 min / 1 season is average time in overall data, but we see different countries have different affinity and tolerance towards content duration/length .
# We see top directors and actors based on genres too this can help us in shortlisting talent in future

# 8. Recommendations (10 Points) - Actionable items for business. No technical jargon. No complications. Simple action items that everyone can understand
# Launch movies in India in 12 month,Japan in 9 month ,South korea, USA and UK in 1-2 months.
# For introducing content to country refer to the countries affinity to the genre
# Introducing content in the appropriate genre may mostly result in the perfect recommendation
# Top actors in genres can assist in shortlisting new content that has to be launched
